<statement>
<p>A triangle has sides with lengths <m>\displaystyle{a}={6.00}</m>, <m>\displaystyle{b}={7.36}</m>, and <m>\displaystyle{c}={6.78}</m>. Calculate all of the angles of this triangle.</p>
<p>A=<fillin characters="4" /> (across from side of length <m>\displaystyle{a}={6.00}</m>)</p>
<p>
  B=<fillin characters="4" /> (across from side of length <m>\displaystyle{b}={7.36}</m>)</p>
<p>
  C=<fillin characters="4" /> (across from side of length <m>\displaystyle{c}={6.78}</m>)</p>
<p>Round to two decimal places.</p>


</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>50.01</li><li>70.02</li><li>57.09</li></ul></p><p>Because we have all three sides, we can use the law of cosines for the first angle.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{6}^{{2}}={7.36}^{{2}}+{6.78}^{{2}}-{2}{\left({7.36}\right)}{\left({6.78}\right)}{\cos{{\left({A}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{36}={54.1696}+{45.9684}-{99.8016}{\cos{{\left({A}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{64.138}=-{99.8016}{\cos{{\left({A}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{0.64265502757471}={\cos{{\left({A}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{A}={50.009915670062}={50.01}</m>.</p>
<p>For a second angle, we can use the shorter law of sines.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle\frac{{\sin{{\left({50.009915670062}\right)}}}}{{6.00}}=\frac{{\sin{{\left({B}\right)}}}}{{7.36}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{0.31009376164396}={\sin{{\left({B}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{B}={\arcsin{{\left(-{0.31009376164396}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{B}={70.020951564616}\approx{70.02}</m></p>
<p>The third angle we can calculate using the angle sum property.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{50.009915670062}+{70.020951564616}+{C}={180}^{\circ}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{C}={57.092847956343}\approx{57.09}</m></p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

